                </fr:date>
                <fr:title text="Problem Formulation">Problem Formulation</fr:title>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>21</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6002/</fr:uri>
                    <fr:display-uri>opt-6002</fr:display-uri>
                    <fr:route>/opt-6002/</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Bolza Problem">Bolza Problem</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <html:p>
    Bolza problem is a fundamental formulation in the calculus of variations and optimal control that minimizes a cost functional consisting of both an integral term (running cost) and a terminal cost. It is described with a system dynamic funcation and a cost function. <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\dot {\mathbf {x}} = f(\mathbf {x}, \mathbf {u}),\quad  \mathbf {x} (0) = x_0]]></fr:tex><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[J := \int _0^{t_f} L \big (\mathbf {x}(t), \mathbf {u}(t)\big ) dt + \Phi  \left ( \mathbf {x}(t_f) \right )]]></fr:tex> where state <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {x}(t)\in  \mathbb {R}^n]]></fr:tex>, control <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {u}(t)\in  \mathbb {R}^k]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L:\mathbb {R}^n \times  \mathbb {R}^k \to  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> is the running cost and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Phi :\mathbb {R}^n \to  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> is the terminal cost. The goal is to find the optimal control <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {u}^*(t)\in  \mathbb {R}^k]]></fr:tex> that minimizes this cost functional subject to the system dynamics and boundary conditions. With input constraint, we minimize <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[J]]></fr:tex> subject to constraints <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {u}(t) \in  U_t \subseteq  \mathbb {R} ^k]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U_t]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:link href="/opt-6006/" title="Admissible control" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6006/" display-uri="opt-6006" type="local">set of admissible control</fr:link> at time <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[t]]></fr:tex> and is guaranteed to be <fr:link href="/gtop-0008/" title="Compactness" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0008/" display-uri="gtop-0008" type="local">compact</fr:link> and convex.
</html:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>3</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>7</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6006/</fr:uri>
                    <fr:display-uri>opt-6006</fr:display-uri>
                    <fr:route>/opt-6006/</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Admissible control">Admissible control</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <html:p>
We say that a control <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {u}]]></fr:tex> is admissible if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  t \in  [0, t_f],\ \mathbf {u}(t) \in  U_t]]></fr:tex> where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U_t]]></fr:tex> is the control constraint set.
</html:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>21</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:title text="Necessary Conditions">Necessary Conditions</fr:title>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>22</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6003/</fr:uri>
                    <fr:display-uri>opt-6003</fr:display-uri>
                    <fr:route>/opt-6003/</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="First-order Variation of the Bolza Functional">First-order Variation of the Bolza Functional</fr:title>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <html:p>
    To find the optimal control <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {u}]]></fr:tex>, we consider the first-order variation of the functional <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[J]]></fr:tex> with respect to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {u}]]></fr:tex>. By augmenting the cost functional with system dynamics <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\dot {\mathbf {x}} = f(\mathbf {x}, \mathbf {u})]]></fr:tex> using the <fr:link href="/opt-6009/" title="Costate Equation" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6009/" display-uri="opt-6009" type="local">costate</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {p}]]></fr:tex>, we define:
</html:p>
                    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
    \frac {\partial  J}{\partial  \mathbf {u}} = \left ( \frac {\partial  f}{\partial  \mathbf {u}} \right )^\intercal  \mathbf {p} + \left ( \frac {\partial  L}{\partial  \mathbf {u}} \right )^\intercal 
]]></fr:tex>
                    <html:p>
    We obtain the stationarity condition <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\frac {\partial  J}{\partial  \mathbf {u}} \equiv  0]]></fr:tex>. See the <fr:link href="/opt-6010/" title="Derivation of the First-order Variation" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6010/" display-uri="opt-6010" type="local">derivation</fr:link> for how this expression arises from first principles.
</html:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>2</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>22</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6004/</fr:uri>
                    <fr:display-uri>opt-6004</fr:display-uri>
                    <fr:route>/opt-6004/</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Optimality Conditions for Bolza Problem">Optimality Conditions for Bolza Problem</fr:title>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <html:p>
    The necessary conditions for the optimality of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {u}(t)]]></fr:tex> are given by the following set of equations:
</html:p>
                    <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                      <fr:frontmatter>
                        <fr:authors>
                          <fr:author>
                            <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
                          </fr:author>
                        </fr:authors>
                        <fr:date>
                          <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                          <fr:month>3</fr:month>
                          <fr:day>8</fr:day>
                        </fr:date>
                        <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6011/</fr:uri>
                        <fr:display-uri>opt-6011</fr:display-uri>
                        <fr:route>/opt-6011/</fr:route>
                        <fr:title text="State Equation">State Equation</fr:title>
                        <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                      </fr:frontmatter>
                      <fr:mainmatter>
                        <html:p>
                          <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\dot {\mathbf {x}}=f(\mathbf {x}, \mathbf {u}),\quad  \mathbf {x}(0)=x_0]]></fr:tex>
                        </html:p>
                      </fr:mainmatter>
                    </fr:tree>
                    <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                      <fr:frontmatter>
                        <fr:authors>
                          <fr:author>
                            <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
                          </fr:author>
                        </fr:authors>
                        <fr:date>
                          <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                          <fr:month>3</fr:month>
                          <fr:day>7</fr:day>
                        </fr:date>
                        <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6009/</fr:uri>
                        <fr:display-uri>opt-6009</fr:display-uri>
                        <fr:route>/opt-6009/</fr:route>
                        <fr:title text="Costate Equation">Costate Equation</fr:title>
                        <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                      </fr:frontmatter>
                      <fr:mainmatter>
                        <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\dot {\mathbf {p}} = -\left ( \frac {\partial  f}{\partial  \mathbf {x}} \right )^\intercal  \mathbf {p} - \left ( \frac {\partial  L}{\partial  \mathbf {x}} \right )^\intercal , \quad  \mathbf {p}(t_f) = \nabla  \Phi \left ( \mathbf {x}(t_f) \right )]]></fr:tex>
                      </fr:mainmatter>
                    </fr:tree>
                    <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                      <fr:frontmatter>
                        <fr:authors>
                          <fr:author>
                            <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
                          </fr:author>
                        </fr:authors>
                        <fr:date>
                          <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                          <fr:month>3</fr:month>
                          <fr:day>8</fr:day>
                        </fr:date>
                        <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6012/</fr:uri>
                        <fr:display-uri>opt-6012</fr:display-uri>
                        <fr:route>/opt-6012/</fr:route>
                        <fr:title text="Stationarity Condition">Stationarity Condition</fr:title>
                        <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                      </fr:frontmatter>
                      <fr:mainmatter>
                        <html:p>
                          <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\left (\frac {\partial  f}{\partial  \mathbf {u}}\right )^\intercal  \mathbf {p} + \left (\frac {\partial  L}{\partial  \mathbf {u}}\right )^\intercal  \equiv  0]]></fr:tex>
                        </html:p>
                      </fr:mainmatter>
                    </fr:tree>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
