                    <fr:title text="Relaxed Control">Relaxed Control</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <html:p>
Consider the <fr:link href="/opt-6002/" title="Bolza Problem" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/opt-6002/" display-uri="opt-6002" type="local">bolza problem</fr:link> subject to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\dot {\mathbf {x}} (t) = f(t,\mathbf {x} (t), \mathbf {u} (t)),\ \mathbf {u} (t) \in  U]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="/gtop-0008/" title="Compactness" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0008/" display-uri="gtop-0008" type="local">compact</fr:link> <fr:link href="/gtop-0009/" title="Metric Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0009/" display-uri="gtop-0009" type="local">metric space</fr:link>.
</html:p>
                    <html:p>
Relaxed controls replace the set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> by the space of <fr:link href="/gtop-000N/" title="Radon Probability Measure" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000N/" display-uri="gtop-000N" type="local">Radon probability measures</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
